  {%- comment -%}── FAQ ──{%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="bfc-ws__section">
    <p class="bfc-ws__section-label">Questions</p>
    <h2>Common questions</h2>

    <div class="bfc-ws__faq">

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What types of stores do you work with?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          We work with film labs, record stores, high-end vintage boutiques, lifestyle and gift shops, art bookstores, photo galleries, museum shops, and any creative retail space where a restored analog camera is a natural fit. We generally don't wholesale to other camera shops.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does "restored" actually mean for your cameras?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          Every camera is refurbished. Some models, such as the AE-1, K1000, and F3, are fully CLA'd to factory standard. Others are refurbished and verified with our in-house professional testing equipment by our repair team. We check shutter accuracy, light seals, meters, and mechanical function. We don't sell as-is — everything that leaves our shop is a working camera.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does the warranty work for my customers?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          All cameras come with a 90-day warranty through BFC. How warranty claims are handled is up to you — your shop can choose to manage the process on behalf of your customers (collect the camera, ship it to us, we repair or replace and return it), or you can have customers contact us directly. Either way works, and we'll accommodate whatever arrangement makes most sense for your shop. One consistent rule: the customer is always responsible for return shipping costs on warranty claims from wholesale orders — that's separate from BFC's direct retail warranty policy.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Can I start with just one camera to try it out?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          Yes. There's no minimum order to get started. A single unit at Standard tier pricing lets you see how it moves in your shop before committing to anything larger. Most of our wholesale partners start with 1–3 units and scale from there.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What's the difference between Grade A and Grade B?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          Grade refers to cosmetic condition only. Grade A cameras have minimal wear and look close to new. Grade B cameras may show light signs of use — small scuffs or brassing — but are mechanically identical to Grade A and carry the same 90-day warranty. Grade B units are priced roughly 10–15% lower, which can work well for certain retail contexts.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Do you do consignment?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          Our standard program is wholesale (you purchase outright). We can discuss consignment arrangements for established partners on a case-by-case basis — reach out and we'll talk through what makes sense for your situation.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bfc-ws__faq-item">
        <button class="bfc-ws__faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What's the restocking timeline?</span>
          <span class="bfc-ws__faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="bfc-ws__faq-a">
          Most models are available within 2–3 weeks of an order being placed. High-demand models (AE-1 Program, Pentax K1000, Olympus Stylus) move fast — we recommend placing orders before you're out of stock rather than after. Large-tier partners get priority allocation on restocks.
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

